Date: 16 November 2016 By: Kaizer NengovhelaViewed: 451One person has been arrested on Wednesday (16 November) for his&nbsp;invovlvement in the matric mathematics question-paper scandal. This follows Minister of Basic Education, Angie Motshekga&#39;s announcement early this week that arrests could be imminent.&nbsp;According to the minister Grade 12 pupils from the Giyani High School, implicated in the leak of the paper, had&nbsp;confessed to having shared it beforehand on WhatsApp.Motshekga made this announcement during a press briefing on Monday. According to the minister, the investigators tracked the information provided by the pupils and this indicated that paper had been leaked from Gauteng to Limpopo.She added that preliminary investigations indicated that a learner from Gauteng had sent the paper to a learner from the Giyani school, seeking the solutions to the paper. She said other learners from the school had&nbsp;also come forward and admitted to having received the question paper from a WhatsApp chat group.&nbsp;Keep on reading the&nbsp;Limpopo Mirror&nbsp;to see how the story unfolds.&nbsp;Kaizer Nengovhela started writing stories for Limpopo Mirror more than a decade ago, in 2 000. Prior to that he had a five year stint at Phala-Phala FM as sports presenter. In 2005 Kaizer received an award from the province&#39;s premier as Best Sports Presenter. The same year he was also nominated as Best Sports Reporter by the Makhado Municipality. Kaizer was awarded the Mathatha Tsedu award in 2014.Email: kaizerdo@webmail.co.zaMore photos... 